    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. Since i'm looking at this from a planning perspective, looking at the climate impact side—is there a consensus among experts that congestion pricing is basically the most effective way to hit those emissions targets in cities? Like, is it seen as a 'must-do' rather than just an option?",
